    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "4b72a0e8_277d3fb5",
        "filename": "snapshot/ios/system_snapshot_ios.cc",
        "patchSetId": 16
      },
      "lineNbr": 204,
      "author": {
        "id": 1116294
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-03-24T21:57:26Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I can\u0027t find authoritative info here, but it seems NX is always enabled for 3rd party iOS apps.  \n\nWhat macOS version do I need to gate on?",
      "parentUuid": "00602405_3ccae2e7",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 203,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 204,
        "endChar": 36
      },
      "revId": "fd9b68bf99c2b793da9c2f5540246a2482643225",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "bcad03bb_a1cb593a",
        "filename": "snapshot/ios/system_snapshot_ios.cc",
        "patchSetId": 16
      },
      "lineNbr": 204,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-03-25T00:41:50Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e I can\u0027t find authoritative info here, but it seems NX is always enabled for 3rd party iOS apps.  \n\u003e \n\u003e What macOS version do I need to gate on?\n\n10.15.0 xnu-6153.11.26/bsd/kern/kern_sysctl.c puts sysctl_nx in “#if DEVELOPMENT || DEBUG”.\n\nIn the previous kernel version we currently have source for, 10.14.3 xnu-4903.241.1/bsd/kern/kern_sysctl.c, sysctl_nx is always available.\n\nIn 10.15.0 again, we can see that it’s always on by looking at osfmk/x86_64/pmap.c, which has “int nx_enabled \u003d 1”. When !DEVELOPMENT \u0026\u0026 !DEBUG, it’s const, even.\n\nSo the control to disable NX disappeared from desktop macOS in 10.15.0, and along with it went the ability to read this sysctl, but it can now be treated as always on. (We should also make this change in SystemSnapshotMac.) On the basis of kernel equivalence, it looks like kern.nx was also present until iOS 13.\n\nWould I expect kern.nx to work on ARM (and iOS) at all? Yes, I would. osfmk/arm/pmap.c has “int nx_enabled \u003d 1” the same as x86_64 (as a const, too, when !DEVELOPMENT \u0026\u0026 !DEBUG).\n\nFor your purposes here, just rework the comment, as a TODO, to say that it’s conditional on OS version, and that we should use kern.nx when available (pre-iOS 13, pre-OS X 10.15 for simulator builds).",
      "parentUuid": "4b72a0e8_277d3fb5",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 203,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 204,
        "endChar": 36
      },
      "revId": "fd9b68bf99c2b793da9c2f5540246a2482643225",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
